        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 2:57PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 256 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Tyus, or 12 miles
southwest of Carrollton, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, dime sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bowdon, Ephesus, Centralhatchee, Roopville, Lowell, Plant Wansley,
Tyus, Blackjack Mountain, and Roosterville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
